In [4]:
# Image Preprocessing function
def preprocess_image(image_path,target_size=(128,128)):
    img=load_img(image_path, target_size=target_size)
    img_array=img_to_array(img)
    img_array /=255.0  # Normalize pixel value
    return img_array
In [5]:
# Prepare data
x=np.stack(df['Image_Path'].apply(preprocess_image).to_numpy())
y=to_categorical(df['Label'].to_numpy(), num_classes=len(label_encoder.classes_))

# Split data into training and testing sets

In [8]:
# Build a simple CNN model
model=Sequential()
model.add(Conv2D(32,(3,3),activation='relu',input_shape=(128,128,3)))
model.add(MaxPooling2D(2,2))
model.add(Flatten())
model.add(Dense(11,activation='softmax'))

In [84]:
classes=df['Label'].unique()

# Number of images to visualize
num_images=1

# Visualize images
for class_label in classes:
    class_images=df[df['Label']==class_label]['Image_Path'].head(num_images).tolist()
    

    # Rows and columns for subplot
    num_rows=1
    num_cols=num_images

    # Craete subplot
    fig,axes=plt.subplots(num_rows,num_cols,figsize=(5,3))

    # Visualize images
    for i in range(num_images):
        image_path=class_images[i]
        # Load and show image
        img=Image.open(image_path)
        axes.imshow(img)
        axes.set_title(f"Class:{class_label}")
        axes.axis('off')

    plt.show()
